miracle-seed.name: Miracle Seed
miracle-seed.effect:
An item to be held by a Pokémon.
It is a seed imbued with life that
ups
the power of Grass-type moves.

blackglasses.name: BlackGlasses
blackglasses.effect:
An item to be held by a Pokémon.
It is a shady-looking pair of glasses
that boosts Dark-type moves.

black-belt.name: Black Belt
black-belt.effect:
An item to be held by a Pokémon.
It is a belt that boosts determinatio
n
and Fighting-type moves.

magnet.name: Magnet
magnet.effect:
An item to be held by a Pokémon.
It is a powerful magnet that boosts
the power of Electric-type moves.

mystic-water.name: Mystic Water
mystic-water.effect:
An item to be held by a Pokémon.
It is a teardrop-shaped gem that ups
the power of Water-type moves.

sharp-beak.name: Sharp Beak
sharp-beak.effect:
An item to be held by a Pokémon.
It is a long, sharp beak that boosts
the power of Flying-type moves.

poison-barb.name: Poison Barb
poison-barb.effect:
An item to be held by a Pokémon.
It is a small, poisonous barb that
ups
the power of Poison-type moves.

nevermeltice.name: NeverMeltIce
nevermeltice.effect:
An item to be held by a Pokémon.
It is a piece of ice that repels heat
and boosts Ice-type moves.

spell-tag.name: Spell Tag
spell-tag.effect:
An item to be held by a Pokémon.
It is a sinister, eerie tag that
boosts
the power of Ghost-type moves.

twistedspoon.name: TwistedSpoon
twistedspoon.effect:
An item to be held by a Pokémon. It
is
a spoon imbued with telekinetic power
that boosts Psychic-type moves.

charcoal.name: Charcoal
charcoal.effect:
An item to be held by a Pokémon.
It is a combustible fuel that boosts
the power of Fire-type moves.

dragon-fang.name: Dragon Fang
dragon-fang.effect:
An item to be held by a Pokémon.
It is a hard and sharp fang that ups
the power of Dragon-type moves.

silk-scarf.name: Silk Scarf
silk-scarf.effect:
An item to be held by a Pokémon.
It is a sumptuous scarf that boosts
the power of Normal-type moves.

up-grade.name: Up-Grade
up-grade.effect:
A transparent device filled with all
sorts of data.
It was produced by Silph Co.

shell-bell.name: Shell Bell
shell-bell.effect:
An item to be held by a Pokémon.
The holder's HP is restored a little
every time it inflicts damage.

sea-incense.name: Sea Incense
sea-incense.effect:
An item to be held by a Pokémon. It
is
incense with a curious aroma that
boosts the power of Water-type moves.

lax-incense.name: Lax Incense
lax-incense.effect:
An item to be held by a Pokémon. The
tricky aroma of this incense lowers
the
foe's accuracy.

lucky-punch.name: Lucky Punch
lucky-punch.effect:
An item to be held by CHANSEY. It is
a
pair of gloves that boosts CHANSEY's
critical-hit ratio.

metal-powder.name: Metal Powder
metal-powder.effect:
An item to be held by DITTO.
Extremely fine yet hard, this odd
powder boosts the Defense stat.

thick-club.name: Thick Club
thick-club.effect:
An item to be held by CUBONE or
MAROWAK. It is a hard bone of some
sort that boosts the Attack stat.

stick.name: Stick
stick.effect:
An item to be held by FARFETCH'D. It
is
a very long and stiff stalk of leek
that boosts the critical-hit ratio.

red-scarf.name: Red Scarf
red-scarf.effect:
An item to be held by a Pokémon.
It boosts the “Cool” aspect of the
holder in a Contest in Sinnoh.

blue-scarf.name: Blue Scarf
blue-scarf.effect:
An item to be held by a Pokémon.
It boosts the “Beauty” aspect of the
holder in a Contest in Sinnoh.

pink-scarf.name: Pink Scarf
pink-scarf.effect:
An item to be held by a Pokémon.
It boosts the “Cute” aspect of the
holder in a Contest in Sinnoh.

green-scarf.name: Green Scarf
green-scarf.effect:
An item to be held by a Pokémon.
It boosts the “Smart” aspect of the
holder in a Contest in Sinnoh.

yellow-scarf.name: Yellow Scarf
yellow-scarf.effect:
An item to be held by a Pokémon.
It boosts the “Tough” aspect of the
holder in a Contest in Sinnoh.

mach-bike.name: Mach Bike
mach-bike.effect:
A folding bicycle that is at least
twice as fast as walking.

coin-case.name: Coin Case
coin-case.effect:
A case for holding coins obtained at
the Game Corner.
It holds up to 50,000 coins.

itemfinder.name: Itemfinder
itemfinder.effect:
A device used for finding items.
If there is a hidden item nearby
when it is used, it emits a signal.

old-rod.name: Old Rod
old-rod.effect:
An old and beat-up fishing rod.
Use it by any body of water to fish
for
wild aquatic Pokémon.

good-rod.name: Good Rod
good-rod.effect:
A new, good-quality fishing rod.
Use it by any body of water to fish
for
wild aquatic Pokémon.

super-rod.name: Super Rod
super-rod.effect:
An awesome, high-tech fishing rod.
Use it by any body of water to fish
for
wild aquatic Pokémon.

s.s.-ticket.name: S.S. Ticket
s.s.-ticket.effect:
The ticket required for sailing on
the
ferry S.S. Aqua. It has a drawing of
a
ship on it.

contest-pass.name: Contest Pass
contest-pass.effect:
The pass required for entering
Pokémon
Contests. It has a drawing of an
award
ribbon on it.

wailmer-pail.name: Wailmer Pail
wailmer-pail.effect:
A nifty watering pail.
Use it to promote strong growth in
BERRIES planted in soft soil.

devon-goods.name: Devon Goods
devon-goods.effect:
A package that contains mechanical
parts of some sort made by the
DEVON CORPORATION.

soot-sack.name: Soot Sack
soot-sack.effect:
A sack used to collect volcanic
ash automatically during walks
over deep ash.

basement-key.name: Basement Key
basement-key.effect:
A key that opens a door in the
Goldenrod Tunnel.

acro-bike.name: Acro Bike
acro-bike.effect:
A folding bicycle that is capable
of stunts like jumps and wheelies.

pokéblock-case.name: Pokéblock Case
pokéblock-case.effect:
A case for holding POKéBLOCKS made
with a BERRY BLENDER. It releases
one POKéBLOCK when shaken.

letter.name: Letter
letter.effect:
An extremely important letter to
STEVEN from the PRESIDENT of the
DEVON CORPORATION.

eon-ticket.name: Eon Ticket
eon-ticket.effect:
The ticket required for sailing on a
ferry to a distant southern island.
It features a drawing of an island.

red-orb.name: Red Orb
red-orb.effect:
A shiny red orb that is said to have
a legend and has a deep connection
with
the Hoenn region.

blue-orb.name: Blue Orb
blue-orb.effect:
A shiny blue orb that is said to have
a legend and has a deep connection
with
the Hoenn region.

scanner.name: Scanner
scanner.effect:
A device used to search for
life-forms in water.
It looks too difficult to use.

go-goggles.name: Go-goggles
go-goggles.effect:
A pair of protective goggles.
They enable a TRAINER to travel
through even desert sandstorms.

meteorite.name: Meteorite
meteorite.effect:
A meteorite that fell from space
onto MT. MOON long ago.
It is very lumpy and hard.

rm.-1-key.name: Rm. 1 Key
rm.-1-key.effect:
A key that opens the door to Room
1 inside the ABANDONED SHIP.
It is old and looks easily broken.

rm.-2-key.name: Rm. 2 Key
rm.-2-key.effect:
A key that opens the door to Room
2 inside the ABANDONED SHIP.
It is old and looks easily broken.

rm.-4-key.name: Rm. 4 Key
rm.-4-key.effect:
A key that opens the door to Room
4 inside the ABANDONED SHIP.
It is old and looks easily broken.

rm.-6-key.name: Rm. 6 Key
rm.-6-key.effect:
A key that opens the door to Room
6 inside the ABANDONED SHIP.
It is old and looks easily broken.

storage-key.name: Storage Key
storage-key.effect:
The key to Team Galactic's sinister
warehouse located at the edge of
Veilstone City.

root-fossil.name: Root Fossil
root-fossil.effect:
A fossil of an ancient Pokémon that
lived in the sea. It appears to be
part of a plant root.

claw-fossil.name: Claw Fossil
claw-fossil.effect:
A fossil of an ancient Pokémon that
lived in the sea. It appears to be
part of a claw.

devon-scope.name: Devon Scope
devon-scope.effect:
A scope that signals the presence
of any unseeable POKéMON.
It is made by the DEVON CORP.

tm---focus-punch.name: TM - Focus Punch
tm---focus-punch.effect:
The user focuses its mind before
launching a punch. It will fail if
the user is hit before it is used.

tm---dragon-claw.name: TM - Dragon Claw
tm---dragon-claw.effect:
The user slashes the target with
huge, sharp claws.

tm---water-pulse.name: TM - Water Pulse
tm---water-pulse.effect:
The user attacks the target with a
pulsing blast of water. It may also
confuse the target.

tm---calm-mind.name: TM - Calm Mind
tm---calm-mind.effect:
The user quietly focuses its mind
and calms its spirit to raise its
Sp. Atk and Sp. Def stats.

tm---roar.name: TM - Roar
tm---roar.effect:
The target is scared off and
replaced by another Pokémon in its
party. In the wild, the battle
ends.

tm---toxic.name: TM - Toxic
tm---toxic.effect:
A move that leaves the target badly
poisoned. Its poison damage worsens
every turn.

tm---snowscape.name: TM - Snowscape
tm---snowscape.effect:
A snowstorm forms on the field for 5
turns. Snow boosts the Defense stat
of Ice-types by 50%.

tm---bulk-up.name: TM - Bulk Up
tm---bulk-up.effect:
The user tenses its muscles to bulk
up its body, boosting both its
Attack and Defense stats.

tm---bullet-seed.name: TM - Bullet Seed
tm---bullet-seed.effect:
The user forcefully shoots seeds at
the target. Two to five seeds are
shot in rapid succession.

tm---hidden-power.name: TM - Hidden Power
tm---hidden-power.effect:
An attack which varies in type
depending on its user. Its type may
be changed with 40 Gems.

tm---sunny-day.name: TM - Sunny Day
tm---sunny-day.effect:
The user intensifies the sun for
five turns, powering up Fire-type
moves.

tm---taunt.name: TM - Taunt
tm---taunt.effect:
The target is taunted into a rage
that allows it to use only attack
moves for three turns.

tm---ice-beam.name: TM - Ice Beam
tm---ice-beam.effect:
The target is struck with an
icy-cold beam of energy. It may
also freeze the target solid.

tm---blizzard.name: TM - Blizzard
tm---blizzard.effect:
A howling blizzard is summoned to
strike the opposing team. It may
also freeze them solid.

tm---hyper-beam.name: TM - Hyper Beam
tm---hyper-beam.effect:
The target is attacked with a
powerful beam. The user must rest
on the next turn to regain its
energy.

tm---light-screen.name: TM - Light Screen
tm---light-screen.effect:
A wondrous wall of light is put up
to suppress damage from special
attacks for five turns.

tm---protect.name: TM - Protect
tm---protect.effect:
It enables the user to evade all
attacks. Its chance of failing
rises if it is used in succession.

tm---rain-dance.name: TM - Rain Dance
tm---rain-dance.effect:
The user summons a heavy rain that
falls for five turns, powering up
Water-type moves.

tm---giga-drain.name: TM - Giga Drain
tm---giga-drain.effect:
A nutrient-draining attack. The
user's HP is restored by half the
damage taken by the target.

tm---safeguard.name: TM - Safeguard
tm---safeguard.effect:
The user creates a protective field
that prevents status problems for
five turns.

tm---frustration.name: TM - Frustration
tm---frustration.effect:
A full-power attack that grows more
powerful the less the user likes
its Trainer.

tm---solarbeam.name: TM - SolarBeam
tm---solarbeam.effect:
A two-turn attack. The user gathers
light, then blasts a bundled beam
on the second turn.

tm---iron-tail.name: TM - Iron Tail
tm---iron-tail.effect:
The target is slammed with a
steel-hard tail. It may also lower
the target's Defense stat.

tm---thunderbolt.name: TM - Thunderbolt
tm---thunderbolt.effect:
A strong electric blast is loosed at
the target. It may also leave the
target with paralysis.

tm---thunder.name: TM - Thunder
tm---thunder.effect:
A wicked thunderbolt is dropped on
the target to inflict damage. It
may also leave the target with
paralysis.

tm---earthquake.name: TM - Earthquake
tm---earthquake.effect:
The user sets off an earthquake that
strikes those around it.

tm---return.name: TM - Return
tm---return.effect:
A full-power attack that grows more
powerful the more the user likes
its Trainer.

tm---dig.name: TM - Dig
tm---dig.effect:
The user burrows, then attacks on
the second turn. It can also be
used to exit dungeons.

tm---psychic.name: TM - Psychic
tm---psychic.effect:
The target is hit by a strong
telekinetic force. It may also
reduce the target's Sp. Def stat.

tm---shadow-ball.name: TM - Shadow Ball
tm---shadow-ball.effect:
The user hurls a shadowy blob at the
target. It may also lower the
target's Sp. Def stat.

tm---brick-break.name: TM - Brick Break
tm---brick-break.effect:
The user attacks with a swift chop.
It can also break any barrier such
as Light Screen and Reflect.

tm---double-team.name: TM - Double Team
tm---double-team.effect:
By moving rapidly, the user makes
illusory copies of itself to raise
its evasiveness.

tm---reflect.name: TM - Reflect
tm---reflect.effect:
A wondrous wall of light is put up
to suppress damage from physical
attacks for five turns.

tm---shock-wave.name: TM - Shock Wave
tm---shock-wave.effect:
The user strikes the target with a
quick jolt of electricity. This
attack cannot be evaded.

tm---flamethrower.name: TM - Flamethrower
tm---flamethrower.effect:
The target is scorched with an
intense blast of fire. It may also
leave the target with a burn.

tm---sludge-bomb.name: TM - Sludge Bomb
tm---sludge-bomb.effect:
Unsanitary sludge is hurled at the
target. It may also poison the
target.

tm---sandstorm.name: TM - Sandstorm
tm---sandstorm.effect:
A five-turn sandstorm is summoned to
hurt all combatants except the
Rock, Ground, and Steel types.

tm---fire-blast.name: TM - Fire Blast
tm---fire-blast.effect:
The target is attacked with an
intense blast of all-consuming
fire. It may also leave the target
with a burn.

tm---rock-tomb.name: TM - Rock Tomb
tm---rock-tomb.effect:
Boulders are hurled at the target.
It also lowers the target's Speed
by preventing its movement.

tm---aerial-ace.name: TM - Aerial Ace
tm---aerial-ace.effect:
The user confounds the target with
speed, then slashes. The attack
lands without fail.

tm---torment.name: TM - Torment
tm---torment.effect:
The user torments and enrages the
target, making it incapable of
using the same move twice in a
row.

tm---facade.name: TM - Facade
tm---facade.effect:
An attack move that doubles its
power if the user is poisoned,
burned, or has paralysis.

tm---secret-power.name: TM - Secret Power
tm---secret-power.effect:
The user attacks the target with a
secret power. Its added effects
vary depending on the user's
environment.

tm---rest.name: TM - Rest
tm---rest.effect:
The user goes to sleep for two
turns. It fully restores the user's
HP and heals any status problem.

tm---attract.name: TM - Attract
tm---attract.effect:
If it is the opposite gender of the
user, the target becomes infatuated
and less likely to attack.

tm---thief.name: TM - Thief
tm---thief.effect:
An attack which steals the foe's
held item if the user isn't already
holding one. Its effects are
temporary when stealing from
Trainers.

tm---steel-wing.name: TM - Steel Wing
tm---steel-wing.effect:
The target is hit with wings of
steel. It may also raise the user's
Defense stat.

tm---skill-swap.name: TM - Skill Swap
tm---skill-swap.effect:
The user employs its psychic power
to exchange Abilities with the
target.

tm---snatch.name: TM - Snatch
tm---snatch.effect:
The user steals the effects of any
healing or stat-changing move the
opponent attempts to use.

tm---overheat.name: TM - Overheat
tm---overheat.effect:
The user attacks the target at full
power. The attack's recoil harshly
reduces the user's Sp. Atk stat.

hm---cut.name: HM - Cut
hm---cut.effect:
The target is cut with a scythe or a
claw. It can also be used to cut
down thin trees.

hm---fly.name: HM - Fly
hm---fly.effect:
The user soars, then strikes its
target on the second turn. It can
also be used for flying to any
familiar town.

hm---surf.name: HM - Surf
hm---surf.effect:
It swamps the area around the user
with a giant wave. It can also be
used for crossing water.

hm---strength.name: HM - Strength
hm---strength.effect:
The target is slugged with a punch
thrown at maximum power. It can
also be used to move heavy
boulders.

hm---flash.name: HM - Flash
hm---flash.effect:
The user flashes a bright light that
cuts the target's accuracy. It can
also be used to illuminate caves.

hm---rock-smash.name: HM - Rock Smash
hm---rock-smash.effect:
The user attacks with a punch that
can shatter a rock. It may also
lower the target's Defense stat.

hm---waterfall.name: HM - Waterfall
hm---waterfall.effect:
The user charges at the target and
may make it flinch. It can also be
used to climb a waterfall.

hm---dive.name: HM - Dive
hm---dive.effect:
Diving on the first turn, the user
floats up and attacks on the second
turn. It can be used to dive deep
in the ocean.

oak's-parcel.name: Oak'S Parcel
oak's-parcel.effect:
A parcel to be delivered to PROF.
OAK from VIRIDIAN CITY's POKéMON
MART.

poké-flute.name: Poké Flute
poké-flute.effect:
A flute that is said to instantly
awaken any POKéMON. It has a
lovely tone.

secret-key.name: Secret Key
secret-key.effect:
A high-tech key that has to be used
at
a specific location. It emits a
special
electric signal to open a door.

bike-voucher.name: Bike Voucher
bike-voucher.effect:
Take this voucher to the BIKE SHOP
in CERULEAN CITY and exchange it
for a bicycle.

gold-teeth.name: Gold Teeth
gold-teeth.effect:
A set of false teeth lost by the
SAFARI ZONE'S WARDEN. It makes his
smile sparkle.

old-amber.name: Old Amber
old-amber.effect:
A piece of amber that contains the
genetic material of an ancient
Pokémon.
It is clear with a reddish tint.

card-key.name: Card Key
card-key.effect:
A card key that opens a shutter in
the
Radio Tower.

lift-key.name: Lift Key
lift-key.effect:
A key that operates the elevator
in TEAM ROCKET's HIDEOUT.
It bears the TEAM ROCKET logo.

helix-fossil.name: Helix Fossil
helix-fossil.effect:
A fossil of an ancient Pokémon that
lived in the sea. It appears to be
part of a seashell.

dome-fossil.name: Dome Fossil
dome-fossil.effect:
A fossil of an ancient Pokémon that
lived in the sea. It appears to be
part of a shell.

silph-scope.name: Silph Scope
silph-scope.effect:
A scope that makes unseeable
POKéMON visible.
It is made by SILPH CO.

bicycle.name: Bicycle
bicycle.effect:
A folding Bicycle that enables much
faster movement than the Running
Shoes.

town-map.name: Town Map
town-map.effect:
A very convenient map that can be
viewed anytime. It even shows your
present location.

vs-seeker.name: Vs Seeker
vs-seeker.effect:
A device that indicates TRAINERS
who want to battle. The battery
charges while traveling.

fame-checker.name: Fame Checker
fame-checker.effect:
A device that enables you to
recall what you've heard and seen
about famous people.

tm-case.name: Tm Case
tm-case.effect:
A case that holds TMs and HMs.
It is attached to the BAG's
compartment for important items.

berry-pouch.name: Berry Pouch
berry-pouch.effect:
A pouch for carrying BERRIES.
It is attached to the BAG's
compartment for important items.

teachy-tv.name: Teachy Tv
teachy-tv.effect:
A television set that is tuned to
a program with useful tips for
novice TRAINERS.

tri-pass.name: Tri-pass
tri-pass.effect:
A pass for ferries between ONE,
TWO, and THREE ISLAND.
It has a drawing of three islands.

rainbow-pass.name: Rainbow Pass
rainbow-pass.effect:
A pass for ferries between
VERMILION and the SEVII ISLANDS.
It features a drawing of a rainbow.

tea.name: Tea
tea.effect:
An aromatic tea prepared by an old
lady. It will slake even the worst
thirst.

mysticticket.name: Mysticticket
mysticticket.effect:
A ticket required to board the ship
to NAVEL ROCK.
It glows with a mystic light.

auroraticket.name: Auroraticket
auroraticket.effect:
A ticket required to board the ship
to BIRTH ISLAND.
It glows beautifully.

powder-jar.name: Powder Jar
powder-jar.effect:
A jar for storing BERRY POWDER
made using a BERRY CRUSHER.

ruby.name: Ruby
ruby.effect:
An exquisitely beautiful gem that
has a red glow.
It symbolizes passion.

sapphire.name: Sapphire
sapphire.effect:
An exquisitely beautiful gem that
has a blue glow.
It symbolizes honesty.

training-link.name: Training Link
training-link.effect:
When held by a Pokémon, it prevents
the holder from gaining any EXP, but
doubles EV gain.

The holder may gain EVs even if they
don't participate in the battle.

name-change-contract.name: Name Change Contract
name-change-contract.effect:
An item which can be used to change
your character's name.

Can only be used once.

mystery-box.name: Mystery Box
mystery-box.effect:
A mysterious box which contains an
unknown reward.

Use to open.

makeover-kit.name: Makeover Kit
makeover-kit.effect:
An item which can be used to change
your character's base appearance.

Can only be used once.

team-name-change-plaque.name: Team Name Change Plaque
team-name-change-plaque.effect:
An item which can be used to change
your team's name and tag.

Can only be used once.
Must be used by team leader.

brace---hp.name: Brace - HP
brace---hp.effect:
An item to be held by a Pokémon when
breeding.
Holding this item will make the
Pokémon's Hp IV the dominant trait.

This item is consumed upon use.

brace---attack.name: Brace - Attack
brace---attack.effect:
An item to be held by a Pokémon when
breeding.
Holding this item will make the
Pokémon's Attack IV the dominant
trait.

This item is consumed upon use.

brace---defense.name: Brace - Defense
brace---defense.effect:
An item to be held by a Pokémon when
breeding.
Holding this item will make the
Pokémon's Defense IV the dominant
trait.

This item is consumed upon use.

brace---sp.atk.name: Brace - Sp.Atk
brace---sp.atk.effect:
An item to be held by a Pokémon when
breeding.
Holding this item will make the
Pokémon's Special Attack IV the
dominant trait.

This item is consumed upon use.

brace---sp.def.name: Brace - Sp.Def
brace---sp.def.effect:
An item to be held by a Pokémon when
breeding.
Holding this item will make the
Pokémon's Special Defense IV the
dominant trait.

This item is consumed upon use.

brace---speed.name: Brace - Speed
brace---speed.effect:
An item to be held by a Pokémon when
breeding.
Holding this item will make the
Pokémon's Speed IV the dominant
trait.

This item is consumed upon use.

ability-pill.name: Ability Pill
ability-pill.effect:
A pill that can be used to switch the
ability of a Pokémon.

Consumed on use.

goodie-bag-(2015).name: Goodie Bag (2015)
goodie-bag-(2015).effect:
A scary looking goodie bag which
contains an unknown reward.

May contain exclusive items for
Halloween 2015. Use to open.

big-robot-part.name: Big Robot Part
big-robot-part.effect:
A large piece of a robot.

It's really heavy!

tiny-robot-part.name: Tiny Robot Part
tiny-robot-part.effect: A small piece of a robot.

xmas-present-(2015).name: Xmas Present (2015)
xmas-present-(2015).effect:
A fancy looking present which contains
an unknown reward.

May contain exclusive items for Xmas
2015. Use to open.

donator-status-ticket---7-days.name: Donator Status Ticket - 7 DAYS
donator-status-ticket---7-days.effect:
An item which can be used to promote
your account to Donator Status.

Donator Status benefits include:
+25% EXP in battles.

tm---roost.name: TM - Roost
tm---roost.effect:
The user lands and rests its body.
It restores the user's HP by up to
half of its max HP.

tm---brine.name: TM - Brine
tm---brine.effect:
If the target's HP is down to about
half, this attack will hit with
double the power.

tm---endure.name: TM - Endure
tm---endure.effect:
The user endures any attack with at
least 1 HP. Its chance of failing
rises if it is used in succession.

tm---dragon-pulse.name: TM - Dragon Pulse
tm---dragon-pulse.effect:
The target is attacked with a shock
wave generated by the user's gaping
mouth.

tm---drain-punch.name: TM - Drain Punch
tm---drain-punch.effect:
An energy-draining punch. The user's
HP is restored by half the damage
taken by the target.

tm---silver-wind.name: TM - Silver Wind
tm---silver-wind.effect:
The target is attacked with powdery
scales blown by wind. It may also
raise all the user's stats.

tm---recycle.name: TM - Recycle
tm---recycle.effect:
The user recycles a held item that
has been used in battle so it can
be used again.

tm---avalanche.name: TM - Avalanche
tm---avalanche.effect:
An attack move that inflicts double
the damage if the user has been
hurt by the target in the same
turn.

tm---stealth-rock.name: TM - Stealth Rock
tm---stealth-rock.effect:
The user lays a trap of levitating
stones around the opponent's team.
The trap hurts opponents that
switch into battle.

tm---captivate.name: TM - Captivate
tm---captivate.effect:
If it is the opposite gender of the
user, the target is charmed into
harshly lowering its Sp. Atk stat.

tm---dark-pulse.name: TM - Dark Pulse
tm---dark-pulse.effect:
The user releases a horrible aura
imbued with dark thoughts. It may
also make the target flinch.

tm---sleep-talk.name: TM - Sleep Talk
tm---sleep-talk.effect:
While it is asleep, the user
randomly uses one of the moves it
knows.

tm---natural-gift.name: TM - Natural Gift
tm---natural-gift.effect:
The user draws power to attack by
using its held Berry. The Berry
determines its type and power.

tm---leech-life.name: TM - Leech Life
tm---leech-life.effect:
The user drains the target's blood.
The user's HP is restored by half
the damage taken by the target.

tm---nature-power.name: TM - Nature Power
tm---nature-power.effect:
An attack that makes use of nature's
power. Its effects vary depending
on the user's environment.

tm---air-slash.name: TM - Air Slash
tm---air-slash.effect:
The user attacks with a blade of air
that slices even the sky. It may
also make the target flinch.

tm---bug-buzz.name: TM - Bug Buzz
tm---bug-buzz.effect:
The user vibrates its wings to
generate a damaging sound wave. It
may also lower the target's Sp. Def
stat.

tm---power-gem.name: TM - Power Gem
tm---power-gem.effect:
The user attacks with a ray of light
that sparkles as if it were made of
gemstones.

tm---razor-wind.name: TM - Razor Wind
tm---razor-wind.effect:
A two-turn attack. Blades of wind
hit opposing Pokémon on the second
turn. Critical hits land more
easily.

tm---brave-bird.name: TM - Brave Bird
tm---brave-bird.effect:
The user tucks in its wings and
charges from a low altitude. The
user also takes serious damage.

tm---whirlwind.name: TM - Whirlwind
tm---whirlwind.effect:
The target is blown away, to be
replaced by another Pokémon in its
party. In the wild, the battle
ends.

tm---nasty-plot.name: TM - Nasty Plot
tm---nasty-plot.effect:
The user stimulates its brain by
thinking bad thoughts. It sharply
raises the user's Sp. Atk.

tm---thunder-fang.name: TM - Thunder Fang
tm---thunder-fang.effect:
The user bites with electrified
fangs. It may also make the target
flinch or leave it with paralysis.

tm---ice-fang.name: TM - Ice Fang
tm---ice-fang.effect:
The user bites with cold-infused
fangs. It may also make the target
flinch or leave it frozen.

tm---fire-fang.name: TM - Fire Fang
tm---fire-fang.effect:
The user bites with flame-cloaked
fangs. It may also make the target
flinch or leave it burned.

tm---psycho-cut.name: TM - Psycho Cut
tm---psycho-cut.effect:
The user tears at the target with
blades formed by psychic power.
Critical hits land more easily.

tm---horn-drill.name: TM - Horn Drill
tm---horn-drill.effect:
The user stabs the target with a
horn that rotates like a drill. If
it hits, the target faints
instantly.

tm---take-down.name: TM - Take Down
tm---take-down.effect:
A reckless, full-body charge attack
for slamming into the target. It
also damages the user a little.

tm---leaf-storm.name: TM - Leaf Storm
tm---leaf-storm.effect:
The user whips up a storm of leaves
around the target. The attack's
recoil harshly reduces the user's
Sp. Atk stat.

tm---power-whip.name: TM - Power Whip
tm---power-whip.effect:
The user violently whirls its vines
or tentacles to harshly lash the
target.

tm---pin-missile.name: TM - Pin Missile
tm---pin-missile.effect:
Sharp spikes are shot at the target
in rapid succession. They hit two
to five times in a row.

tm---cross-poison.name: TM - Cross Poison
tm---cross-poison.effect:
A slashing attack with a poisonous
blade that may also leave the
target poisoned. Critical hits land
more easily.

tm---water-gun.name: TM - Water Gun
tm---water-gun.effect:
The target is blasted with a
forceful shot of water.

tm---hydro-pump.name: TM - Hydro Pump
tm---hydro-pump.effect:
The target is blasted by a huge
volume of water launched under
great pressure.

tm---bubblebeam.name: TM - BubbleBeam
tm---bubblebeam.effect:
A spray of bubbles is forcefully
ejected at the opposing team. It
may also lower their Speed stats.

tm---submission.name: TM - Submission
tm---submission.effect:
The user grabs the target and
recklessly dives for the ground. It
also hurts the user slightly.

tm---mega-drain.name: TM - Mega Drain
tm---mega-drain.effect:
A nutrient-draining attack. The
user's HP is restored by half the
damage taken by the target.

tm---dragon-rage.name: TM - Dragon Rage
tm---dragon-rage.effect:
This attack hits the target with a
shock wave of pure rage. This
attack always inflicts 40 HP
damage.

tm---fire-spin.name: TM - Fire Spin
tm---fire-spin.effect:
The target becomes trapped within a
fierce vortex of fire that rages
for four to five turns.

tm---heavy-slam.name: TM - Heavy Slam
tm---heavy-slam.effect:
The user slams into the target with
its heavy body. The more the user
outweighs the target, the greater
its damage.

tm---electro-ball.name: TM - Electro Ball
tm---electro-ball.effect:
The user hurls an electric orb at
the target. The faster the user is
than the target, the greater the
damage.

tm---fissure.name: TM - Fissure
tm---fissure.effect:
The user opens up a fissure in the
ground and drops the target in. The
target instantly faints if it
hits.

tm---agility.name: TM - Agility
tm---agility.effect:
The user relaxes and lightens its
body to move faster. It sharply
boosts the Speed stat.

tm---rage.name: TM - Rage
tm---rage.effect:
As long as this move is in use, the
power of rage raises the Attack
stat each time the user is hit in
battle.

tm---teleport.name: TM - Teleport
tm---teleport.effect:
When used by a Trainer, it switches
the user out no matter what. Wild
Pokémon may flee instantly. When
used out of battle, it will warp
you to the last Pokémon Center.

tm---stored-power.name: TM - Stored Power
tm---stored-power.effect:
The user attacks the target with
stored power. The more the user's
stats are raised, the greater the
damage.

tm---hex.name: TM - Hex
tm---hex.effect:
This relentless attack does massive
damage to a target affected by
status problems.

tm---focus-energy.name: TM - Focus Energy
tm---focus-energy.effect:
The user takes a deep breath and
focuses so that critical hits land
more easily.

tm---bide.name: TM - Bide
tm---bide.effect:
The user endures attacks for two
turns, then strikes back to cause
double the damage taken.

tm---egg-bomb.name: TM - Egg Bomb
tm---egg-bomb.effect:
A large egg is hurled at the target
with maximum force to inflict
damage.

tm---skull-bash.name: TM - Skull Bash
tm---skull-bash.effect:
The user tucks in its head to raise
its Defense in the first turn, then
rams the target on the next turn.

tm---amnesia.name: TM - Amnesia
tm---amnesia.effect:
The user temporarily empties its
mind to forget its concerns. It
sharply raises the user's Sp. Def
stat.

tm---razor-shell.name: TM - Razor Shell
tm---razor-shell.effect:
The user cuts its target with sharp
shells. This attack may also lower
the target's Defense stat.

tm---heat-crash.name: TM - Heat Crash
tm---heat-crash.effect:
The user slams its target with its
flame- covered body. The more the
user outweighs the target, the
greater the damage.

tm---tail-slap.name: TM - Tail Slap
tm---tail-slap.effect:
The user attacks by striking the
target with its hard tail. It hits
the target two to five times in a
row.

tm---hurricane.name: TM - Hurricane
tm---hurricane.effect:
The user attacks by wrapping its
opponent in a fierce wind that
flies up into the sky. It may also
confuse the target.

tm---psywave.name: TM - Psywave
tm---psywave.effect:
The target is attacked with an odd
psychic wave. The attack varies in
intensity.

tm---tri-attack.name: TM - Tri Attack
tm---tri-attack.effect:
The user strikes with a simultaneous
three-beam attack. May also burn,
freeze, or leave the target with
paralysis.

tm---curse.name: TM - Curse
tm---curse.effect:
A move which functions differently
depending on the type of its user.
When used by a Ghost, the target
loses 1/4 of their maximum HP every
turn, but the user immediately
loses half of theirs. For other
types, it will reduce Speed while
increasing Attack & Defense by 1
stage.

tm---reversal.name: TM - Reversal
tm---reversal.effect:
An all-out attack that becomes more
powerful the less HP the user has.

tm---scary-face.name: TM - Scary Face
tm---scary-face.effect:
The user frightens the target with a
scary face to harshly reduce its
Speed stat.

tm---spikes.name: TM - Spikes
tm---spikes.effect:
The user lays a trap of spikes at
the opposing team's feet. The trap
hurts Pokémon that switch into
battle.

tm---zap-cannon.name: TM - Zap Cannon
tm---zap-cannon.effect:
The user fires an electric blast
like a cannon to inflict damage and
cause paralysis.

tm---detect.name: TM - Detect
tm---detect.effect:
It enables the user to evade all
attacks. Its chance of failing
rises if it is used in succession.

tm---charm.name: TM - Charm
tm---charm.effect:
The user gazes at the target rather
charmingly, making it less wary.
The target's Attack is harshly
lowered.

tm---megahorn.name: TM - Megahorn
tm---megahorn.effect:
Using its tough and impressive horn,
the user rams into the target with
no letup.

tm---dragonbreath.name: TM - DragonBreath
tm---dragonbreath.effect:
The user exhales a mighty gust that
inflicts damage. It may also leave
the target with paralysis.

tm---baton-pass.name: TM - Baton Pass
tm---baton-pass.effect:
The user switches places with a
Pokémon in your party, passing
along some effects. Will not pass
stat changes or status ailments.

tm---encore.name: TM - Encore
tm---encore.effect:
The user compels the target to keep
using only the move it last used
for three turns.

tm---sweet-scent.name: TM - Sweet Scent
tm---sweet-scent.effect:
Expels a sweet scent which lowers
the foe's Evasion. It lures hordes
of Pokémon when used in areas which
have wild encounters, but requires
more PP.

tm---crunch.name: TM - Crunch
tm---crunch.effect:
Crunches the foe with its sharp
teeth. It may lower their Defense
stat.

tm---future-sight.name: TM - Future Sight
tm---future-sight.effect:
Two turns after this move is used, a
hunk of psychic energy attacks the
target.

tm---whirlpool.name: TM - Whirlpool
tm---whirlpool.effect:
Traps foes in a violent swirling
whirlpool for four to five turns.

tm---beat-up.name: TM - Beat Up
tm---beat-up.effect:
The user gets all party Pokémon to
attack the target. The more party
Pokémon, the greater the number of
attacks.

tm---revenge.name: TM - Revenge
tm---revenge.effect:
An attack move that inflicts double
the damage if the user has been
hurt by the opponent in the same
turn.

tm---imprison.name: TM - Imprison
tm---imprison.effect:
If the opponents know any move also
known by the user, the opponents
are prevented from using it.

tm---screech.name: TM - Screech
tm---screech.effect:
An earsplitting screech harshly
reduces the target's Defense stat.

tm---blaze-kick.name: TM - Blaze Kick
tm---blaze-kick.effect:
The user launches a kick that lands
a critical hit more easily. It may
also leave the target with a burn.

tm---weather-ball.name: TM - Weather Ball
tm---weather-ball.effect:
An attack move that varies in power
and type depending on the weather.

tm---fake-tears.name: TM - Fake Tears
tm---fake-tears.effect:
The user feigns crying to fluster
the target, harshly lowering its
Sp. Def stat.

tm---cosmic-power.name: TM - Cosmic Power
tm---cosmic-power.effect:
The user absorbs a mystical power
from space to raise its Defense and
Sp. Def stats.

tm---sand-tomb.name: TM - Sand Tomb
tm---sand-tomb.effect:
The user traps the target inside a
harshly raging sandstorm for four
to five turns.

tm---muddy-water.name: TM - Muddy Water
tm---muddy-water.effect:
The user attacks by shooting muddy
water at the opposing team. It may
also lower the targets' accuracy.

tm---icicle-spear.name: TM - Icicle Spear
tm---icicle-spear.effect:
The user launches sharp icicles at
the target. It strikes two to five
times in a row.

tm---mud-shot.name: TM - Mud Shot
tm---mud-shot.effect:
The user attacks by hurling a blob
of mud at the target. It also
reduces the target's Speed.

tm---magical-leaf.name: TM - Magical Leaf
tm---magical-leaf.effect:
The user scatters curious leaves
that chase the target. This attack
will not miss.

tm---leaf-blade.name: TM - Leaf Blade
tm---leaf-blade.effect:
The user handles a sharp leaf like a
sword and attacks by cutting its
target. Critical hits land more
easily.

tm---dragon-dance.name: TM - Dragon Dance
tm---dragon-dance.effect:
The user vigorously performs a
mystic, powerful dance that boosts
its Attack and Speed stats.

tm---rock-blast.name: TM - Rock Blast
tm---rock-blast.effect:
The user hurls hard rocks at the
target. Two to five rocks are
launched in quick succession.

tm---close-combat.name: TM - Close Combat
tm---close-combat.effect:
The user fights the target up close
without guarding itself. It also
cuts the user's Defense and Sp.
Def.

tm---assurance.name: TM - Assurance
tm---assurance.effect:
If the target has already taken some
damage in the same turn, this
attack's power is doubled.

tm---power-swap.name: TM - Power Swap
tm---power-swap.effect:
The user employs its psychic power
to switch changes to its Attack and
Sp. Atk with the target.

tm---guard-swap.name: TM - Guard Swap
tm---guard-swap.effect:
The user employs its psychic power
to switch changes to its Defense
and Sp. Def with the target.

tm---pay-day.name: TM - Pay Day
tm---pay-day.effect:
Throws coins at the foe which are
recovered after the battle. The
amount of coins increases with the
foe's level. It's only effective
once per battle.

tm---toxic-spikes.name: TM - Toxic Spikes
tm---toxic-spikes.effect:
The user lays a trap of poison
spikes at the opponent's feet. They
poison opponents that switch into
battle.

tm---flare-blitz.name: TM - Flare Blitz
tm---flare-blitz.effect:
The user cloaks itself in fire and
charges at the target. The user
sustains serious damage and may
leave the target burned.

tm---aura-sphere.name: TM - Aura Sphere
tm---aura-sphere.effect:
The user looses a blast of aura
power from deep within its body at
the target. This move is certain to
hit.

tm---counter.name: TM - Counter
tm---counter.effect:
A retaliation move that counters any
physical attack, inflicting double
the damage taken.

tm---metronome.name: TM - Metronome
tm---metronome.effect:
The user waggles a finger and
stimulates its brain into randomly
using nearly any move.

tm---mega-kick.name: TM - Mega Kick
tm---mega-kick.effect:
The target is attacked by a kick
launched with muscle-packed power.

tm---mega-punch.name: TM - Mega Punch
tm---mega-punch.effect:
The target is slugged by a punch
thrown with muscle-packed power.

tm---double-edge.name: TM - Double-Edge
tm---double-edge.effect:
A reckless, life-risking tackle. It
also damages the user by a fairly
large amount, however.

tm---body-slam.name: TM - Body Slam
tm---body-slam.effect:
The user drops onto the target with
its full body weight. It may also
leave the target with paralysis.

tm---softboiled.name: TM - Softboiled
tm---softboiled.effect:
Heals the user by half of its max
HP.

tm---rollout.name: TM - Rollout
tm---rollout.effect:
The user continually rolls into the
target over five turns. It becomes
stronger each time it hits.

tm---dynamicpunch.name: TM - DynamicPunch
tm---dynamicpunch.effect:
The user punches the target with
full, concentrated power. It
confuses the target if it hits.

tm---mimic.name: TM - Mimic
tm---mimic.effect:
The user copies the target's last
move. The move can be used during
battle until the Pokémon is
switched out.

tm---fury-cutter.name: TM - Fury Cutter
tm---fury-cutter.effect:
The target is slashed with scythes
or claws. Its power increases if it
hits in succession.

tm---seismic-toss.name: TM - Seismic Toss
tm---seismic-toss.effect:
The target is thrown using the power
of gravity. It inflicts damage
equal to the user's level.

tm---mud-slap.name: TM - Mud-Slap
tm---mud-slap.effect:
The user hurls mud in the target's
face to inflict damage and lower
its accuracy.

tm---psybeam.name: TM - Psybeam
tm---psybeam.effect:
The target is attacked with a
peculiar ray. It may also cause
confusion.

tm---confuse-ray.name: TM - Confuse Ray
tm---confuse-ray.effect:
The target is exposed to a sinister
ray that triggers confusion.

tm---poison-tail.name: TM - Poison Tail
tm---poison-tail.effect:
The user hits the target with its
tail. It may also poison the
target. Critical hits land more
easily.

tm---metal-claw.name: TM - Metal Claw
tm---metal-claw.effect:
The target is raked with steel
claws. It may also raise the user's
Attack stat.

tm---swift.name: TM - Swift
tm---swift.effect:
Star-shaped rays are shot at the
opposing team. This attack never
misses.

tm---icy-wind.name: TM - Icy Wind
tm---icy-wind.effect:
The user attacks with a gust of
chilled air. It also reduces the
targets' Speed stat.

tm---air-cutter.name: TM - Air Cutter
tm---air-cutter.effect:
The user launches razor-like wind to
slash the opposing team. Critical
hits land more easily.

tm---night-shade.name: TM - Night Shade
tm---night-shade.effect:
The user makes the target see a
frightening mirage. It inflicts
damage matching the user's level.

tm---foul-play.name: TM - Foul Play
tm---foul-play.effect:
The user turns the target's power
against it. The higher the target's
Attack stat, the greater the
damage.

tm---seed-bomb.name: TM - Seed Bomb
tm---seed-bomb.effect:
The user slams a barrage of
hard-shelled seeds down on the
target from above.

tm---iron-head.name: TM - Iron Head
tm---iron-head.effect:
The user slams the target with its
steel-hard head. It may also make
the target flinch.

tm---gunk-shot.name: TM - Gunk Shot
tm---gunk-shot.effect:
The user shoots filthy garbage at
the target to attack. It may also
poison the target.

tm---iron-defense.name: TM - Iron Defense
tm---iron-defense.effect:
The user hardens its body's surface
like iron, sharply raising its
Defense stat.

tm---drill-run.name: TM - Drill Run
tm---drill-run.effect:
The user crashes into its target
while rotating its body like a
drill. Critical hits land more
easily.

tm---trick.name: TM - Trick
tm---trick.effect:
The user catches the target off
guard and swaps its held item with
its own.

tm---tailwind.name: TM - Tailwind
tm---tailwind.effect:
The user whips up a turbulent
whirlwind that ups the Speed of all
party Pokémon for four turns.

tm---hyper-voice.name: TM - Hyper Voice
tm---hyper-voice.effect:
The user lets loose a horribly
echoing shout with the power to
inflict damage.

tm---heat-wave.name: TM - Heat Wave
tm---heat-wave.effect:
The user attacks by exhaling hot
breath on the opposing team. It may
also leave targets with a burn.

tm---earth-power.name: TM - Earth Power
tm---earth-power.effect:
The user makes the ground under the
target erupt with power. It may
also lower the target's Sp. Def.

tm---outrage.name: TM - Outrage
tm---outrage.effect:
The user rampages and attacks for
two to three turns. It then becomes
confused, however.

tm---draco-meteor.name: TM - Draco Meteor
tm---draco-meteor.effect:
Comets are summoned down from the
sky onto the target. The attack's
recoil harshly reduces the user's
Sp. Atk stat.

tm---fire-punch.name: TM - Fire Punch
tm---fire-punch.effect:
The target is punched with a fiery
fist. It may also leave the target
with a burn.

tm---ice-punch.name: TM - Ice Punch
tm---ice-punch.effect:
The target is punched with an icy
fist. It may also leave the target
frozen.

tm---thunderpunch.name: TM - ThunderPunch
tm---thunderpunch.effect:
The target is punched with an
electrified fist. It may also leave
the target with paralysis.

tm---zen-headbutt.name: TM - Zen Headbutt
tm---zen-headbutt.effect:
The user focuses its willpower to
its head and attacks the target. It
may also make the target flinch.

tm---helping-hand.name: TM - Helping Hand
tm---helping-hand.effect:
The user assists an ally by boosting
the power of its attack.

tm---low-kick.name: TM - Low Kick
tm---low-kick.effect:
A powerful low kick that makes the
target fall over. It inflicts
greater damage on heavier targets.

tm---acid-spray.name: TM - Acid Spray
tm---acid-spray.effect:
The user spits fluid that works to
melt the target. This harshly
reduces the target's Sp. Def stat.

tm---headbutt.name: TM - Headbutt
tm---headbutt.effect:
The user sticks out its head and
attacks by charging straight into
the target. It may also make the
target flinch.

tm---selfdestruct.name: TM - Selfdestruct
tm---selfdestruct.effect:
The user attacks everything around
it by causing an explosion. The
user faints upon using this move.

tm---superpower.name: TM - Superpower
tm---superpower.effect:
The user attacks the target with
great power. However, it also
lowers the user's Attack and
Defense.

tm---charge.name: TM - Charge
tm---charge.effect:
The user charges up, doubling the
power of the next Electric-type
move. It also raises the Sp. Def of
the user by 1 stage.

tm---haze.name: TM - Haze
tm---haze.effect:
The user creates a haze that
eliminates every stat change among
all the Pokémon engaged in battle.

tm---spite.name: TM - Spite
tm---spite.effect:
The user unleashes its grudge on the
move last used by the target by
cutting 4 PP from it.

tm---gravity.name: TM - Gravity
tm---gravity.effect:
Gravity is intensified for five
turns, making moves involving
flying unusable and negating
Levitate.

tm---knock-off.name: TM - Knock Off
tm---knock-off.effect:
The user slaps down the target's
held item, preventing that item
from being used in the battle.

tm---bug-bite.name: TM - Bug Bite
tm---bug-bite.effect:
The user bites the target. If the
target is holding a Berry, the user
eats it and gains its effect.

tm---super-fang.name: TM - Super Fang
tm---super-fang.effect:
The user chomps hard on the target
with its sharp front fangs. It cuts
the target's HP to half.

tm---vacuum-wave.name: TM - Vacuum Wave
tm---vacuum-wave.effect:
The user whirls its fists to send a
wave of pure vacuum at the target.
This move always goes first.

tm---uproar.name: TM - Uproar
tm---uproar.effect:
The user attacks in an uproar for
three turns. Over that time, no one
can fall asleep.

tm---endeavor.name: TM - Endeavor
tm---endeavor.effect:
An attack move that cuts down the
target's HP to equal the user's
HP.

tm---pain-split.name: TM - Pain Split
tm---pain-split.effect:
The user adds its HP to the target's
HP, then equally shares the
combined HP with the target.

tm---featherdance.name: TM - FeatherDance
tm---featherdance.effect:
The user covers the target's body
with a mass of down that harshly
lowers its Attack stat.

tm---metal-sound.name: TM - Metal Sound
tm---metal-sound.effect:
A horrible sound like scraping metal
harshly reduces the target's Sp.
Def stat.

tm---electroweb.name: TM - Electroweb
tm---electroweb.effect:
The user captures and attacks
opposing Pokémon by using an
electric net. It reduces the
targets' Speed stat.

dusk-ball.name: Dusk Ball
dusk-ball.effect:
A somewhat different Poké Ball that
makes it easier to catch wild Pokémon
at night or in dark places like
caves.

heal-ball.name: Heal Ball
heal-ball.effect:
A remedial Poké Ball that restores
the
caught Pokémon's HP and eliminates
any status problem.

quick-ball.name: Quick Ball
quick-ball.effect:
A somewhat different Poké Ball that
provides a better catch rate if it is
used at the start of a wild
encounter.

cherish-ball.name: Cherish Ball
cherish-ball.effect:
A quite rare Poké Ball that has been
specially crafted to commemorate
an occasion of some sort.

old-gateau.name: Old Gateau
old-gateau.effect:
Old Chateau's hidden specialty.
It heals all the status problems of a
single Pokémon.

x-sp.-def.name: X Sp. Def
x-sp.-def.effect:
An item that raises the Sp. Def stat
of a Pokémon in battle. It wears off
if
the Pokémon is withdrawn.

honey.name: Honey
honey.effect:
A sweet honey with a lush aroma that
attracts wild Pokémon when it is used
in grass, caves, or on special trees.

growth-mulch.name: Growth Mulch
growth-mulch.effect:
A fertilizer to be spread on soft
soil.
It speeds up the growth of Berries.
However, it also dries the soil
faster.

damp-mulch.name: Damp Mulch
damp-mulch.effect:
A fertilizer to be spread on soft
soil.
It slows the growth of Berries and
causes the soil to dry slower.

stable-mulch.name: Stable Mulch
stable-mulch.effect:
A fertilizer to be spread on soft
soil.
It extends the time ripened Berries
remain on their plants before
falling.

gooey-mulch.name: Gooey Mulch
gooey-mulch.effect:
A fertilizer to be spread on soft
soil.
It ups the number of times new plants
grow where mature plants withered.

rare-bone.name: Rare Bone
rare-bone.effect:
A bone that is extremely valuable for
Pokémon archaeology. It can be sold
for a high price to shops.

shiny-stone.name: Shiny Stone
shiny-stone.effect:
A peculiar stone that makes certain
species of Pokémon evolve.
It shines with a dazzling light.

dusk-stone.name: Dusk Stone
dusk-stone.effect:
A peculiar stone that makes certain
species of Pokémon evolve.
It is as dark as dark can be.

dawn-stone.name: Dawn Stone
dawn-stone.effect:
A peculiar stone that makes certain
species of Pokémon evolve.
It sparkles like eyes.

oval-stone.name: Oval Stone
oval-stone.effect:
A peculiar stone that makes certain
species of Pokémon evolve.
It is shaped like an egg.

odd-keystone.name: Odd Keystone
odd-keystone.effect:
A vital item that is needed to keep a
stone tower from collapsing. Voices
can be heard from it occasionally.

griseous-orb.name: Griseous Orb
griseous-orb.effect:
A glowing orb to be held by GIRATINA.
It boosts the power of Dragon- and
Ghost-type moves.

douse-drive.name: Douse Drive
douse-drive.effect:
A cassette to be held by Genesect.
It changes Techno Blast to a
Water-type move.

shock-drive.name: Shock Drive
shock-drive.effect:
A cassette to be held by Genesect.
It changes Techno Blast to an
Electric-type move.

burn-drive.name: Burn Drive
burn-drive.effect:
A cassette to be held by Genesect.
It changes Techno Blast to a
Fire-type move.

chill-drive.name: Chill Drive
chill-drive.effect:
A cassette to be held by Genesect.
It changes Techno Blast to an
Ice-type move.

sweet-heart.name: Sweet Heart
sweet-heart.effect:
Very sweet chocolate.
It restores the HP of one Pokémon
by only 20 points.

adamant-orb.name: Adamant Orb
adamant-orb.effect:
A brightly gleaming orb to be held by
DIALGA. It boosts the power of
Dragon-
and Steel-type moves.

lustrous-orb.name: Lustrous Orb
lustrous-orb.effect:
A beautifully glowing orb to be held
by
PALKIA. It boosts the power of
Dragon-
and Water-type moves.

greet-mail.name: Greet Mail
greet-mail.effect:

introductory greetings.
Let a Pokémon hold it for delivery.

favored-mail.name: Favored Mail
favored-mail.effect:
Stationery designed for
writing about your favorite things.
Let a Pokémon hold it for delivery.

rsvp-mail.name: RSVP Mail
rsvp-mail.effect:

invitations.

thanks-mail.name: Thanks Mail
thanks-mail.effect:

a thank-you note.

inquiry-mail.name: Inquiry Mail

writing questions.

like-mail.name: Like Mail
like-mail.effect:

reply-mail.name: Reply Mail
reply-mail.effect:

writing a reply.

bridgemail-d.name: BridgeMail D
bridgemail-d.effect:

a red drawbridge.

bridgemail-t.name: BridgeMail T
bridgemail-t.effect:

wide-lens.name: Wide Lens
wide-lens.effect:
An item to be held by a Pokémon.
It is a magnifying lens that slightly
boosts the accuracy of moves.

muscle-band.name: Muscle Band
muscle-band.effect:
An item to be held by a Pokémon.
It is a headband that slightly boosts
the power of physical moves.

wise-glasses.name: Wise Glasses
wise-glasses.effect:
An item to be held by a Pokémon. It
is
a thick pair of glasses that slightly
boosts the power of special moves.

expert-belt.name: Expert Belt
expert-belt.effect:
An item to be held by a Pokémon. It
is
a well-worn belt that slightly boosts
the power of supereffective moves.

light-clay.name: Light Clay
light-clay.effect:
A Pokémon held item that extends the
duration of barrier moves like Light
Screen and Reflect used by the
holder.

life-orb.name: Life Orb
life-orb.effect:
An item to be held by a Pokémon.
It boosts the power of moves, but at
the cost of some HP on each hit.

power-herb.name: Power Herb
power-herb.effect:
A single-use item to be held by a
Pokémon. It allows the immediate use
of
a move that charges on the first
turn.

toxic-orb.name: Toxic Orb
toxic-orb.effect:
An item to be held by a Pokémon.
It is a bizarre orb that badly
poisons
the holder in battle.

flame-orb.name: Flame Orb
flame-orb.effect:
An item to be held by a Pokémon.
It is a bizarre orb that inflicts a
burn on the holder in battle.

quick-powder.name: Quick Powder
quick-powder.effect:
An item to be held by DITTO.
Extremely fine yet hard, this odd
powder boosts the Speed stat.

focus-sash.name: Focus Sash
focus-sash.effect:
An item to be held by a Pokémon. If
it
has full HP, the holder will endure
one
potential KO attack, leaving 1 HP.

zoom-lens.name: Zoom Lens
zoom-lens.effect:
An item to be held by a Pokémon.
If the holder moves after the foe,
its
accuracy will be boosted.

metronome.name: Metronome
metronome.effect:
A Pokémon held item that boosts a
move
used consecutively. Its effect is
reset if another move is used.

iron-ball.name: Iron Ball
iron-ball.effect:
A Pokémon held item that cuts Speed.
It makes Flying-type and levitating
holders susceptible to Ground moves.

lagging-tail.name: Lagging Tail
lagging-tail.effect:
An item to be held by a Pokémon.
It is tremendously heavy and makes
the holder move slower than usual.

destiny-knot.name: Destiny Knot
destiny-knot.effect:
A long, thin, bright red string to
be held by a Pokémon. If the holder
becomes infatuated, the foe does too.

black-sludge.name: Black Sludge
black-sludge.effect:
A held item that gradually restores
the HP of Poison-type Pokémon.
It inflicts damage on all other
types.

icy-rock.name: Icy Rock
icy-rock.effect:
A Pokémon held item that extends the
duration of the move Hail used by the
holder.

smooth-rock.name: Smooth Rock
smooth-rock.effect:
A Pokémon held item that extends the
duration of the move Sandstorm used
by the holder.

heat-rock.name: Heat Rock
heat-rock.effect:
A Pokémon held item that extends the
duration of the move Sunny Day used
by the holder.

damp-rock.name: Damp Rock
damp-rock.effect:
A Pokémon held item that extends the
duration of the move Rain Dance used
by the holder.

grip-claw.name: Grip Claw
grip-claw.effect:
A Pokémon held item that extends the
duration of multiturn attacks like
Bind and Wrap.

choice-scarf.name: Choice Scarf
choice-scarf.effect:
An item to be held by a Pokémon.
This scarf boosts Speed, but allows
the use of only one kind of move.

sticky-barb.name: Sticky Barb
sticky-barb.effect:
A held item that damages the holder
on
every turn. It may latch on to foes
that touch the holder.

power-bracer.name: Power Bracer
power-bracer.effect:
A Pokémon held item that promotes
Attack gain on leveling, but reduces
the Speed stat.

power-belt.name: Power Belt
power-belt.effect:
A Pokémon held item that promotes
Defense gain on leveling, but reduces
the Speed stat.

power-lens.name: Power Lens
power-lens.effect:
A Pokémon held item that promotes
Sp. Atk gain on leveling, but reduces
the Speed stat.

power-band.name: Power Band
power-band.effect:
A Pokémon held item that promotes
Sp. Def gain on leveling, but reduces
the Speed stat.

power-anklet.name: Power Anklet
power-anklet.effect:
A Pokémon held item that promotes
Speed gain on leveling, but reduces
the Speed stat.

power-weight.name: Power Weight
power-weight.effect:
A Pokémon held item that promotes
HP gain on leveling, but reduces the
Speed stat.

shed-shell.name: Shed Shell
shed-shell.effect:
A tough, discarded carapace to be
held
by a Pokémon. It enables the holder
to
switch with a waiting Pokémon in
battle.

big-root.name: Big Root
big-root.effect:
A Pokémon held item that boosts the
power of HP-stealing moves to let the
holder recover more HP.

choice-specs.name: Choice Specs
choice-specs.effect:
An item to be held by a Pokémon.
These
distinctive glasses boost Sp. Atk,
but
allow only one kind of move to be
used.

flame-plate.name: Flame Plate
flame-plate.effect:
An item to be held by a Pokémon.
It is a stone tablet that boosts the
power of Fire-type moves.

splash-plate.name: Splash Plate
splash-plate.effect:
An item to be held by a Pokémon.
It is a stone tablet that boosts the
power of Water-type moves.

zap-plate.name: Zap Plate
zap-plate.effect:
An item to be held by a Pokémon.
It is a stone tablet that boosts the
power of Electric-type moves.

meadow-plate.name: Meadow Plate
meadow-plate.effect:
An item to be held by a Pokémon.
It is a stone tablet that boosts the
power of Grass-type moves.

icicle-plate.name: Icicle Plate
icicle-plate.effect:
An item to be held by a Pokémon.
It is a stone tablet that boosts the
power of Ice-type moves.

fist-plate.name: Fist Plate
fist-plate.effect:
An item to be held by a Pokémon.
It is a stone tablet that boosts the
power of Fighting-type moves.

toxic-plate.name: Toxic Plate
toxic-plate.effect:
An item to be held by a Pokémon.
It is a stone tablet that boosts the
power of Poison-type moves.

earth-plate.name: Earth Plate
earth-plate.effect:
An item to be held by a Pokémon.
It is a stone tablet that boosts the
power of Ground-type moves.

sky-plate.name: Sky Plate
sky-plate.effect:
An item to be held by a Pokémon.
It is a stone tablet that boosts the
power of Flying-type moves.

mind-plate.name: Mind Plate
mind-plate.effect:
An item to be held by a Pokémon.
It is a stone tablet that boosts the
power of Psychic-type moves.

insect-plate.name: Insect Plate
insect-plate.effect:
An item to be held by a Pokémon.
It is a stone tablet that boosts the
power of Bug-type moves.

stone-plate.name: Stone Plate
stone-plate.effect:
An item to be held by a Pokémon.
It is a stone tablet that boosts the
power of Rock-type moves.

spooky-plate.name: Spooky Plate
spooky-plate.effect:
An item to be held by a Pokémon.
It is a stone tablet that boosts the
power of Ghost-type moves.

draco-plate.name: Draco Plate
draco-plate.effect:
An item to be held by a Pokémon.
It is a stone tablet that boosts the
power of Dragon-type moves.

dread-plate.name: Dread Plate
dread-plate.effect:
An item to be held by a Pokémon.
It is a stone tablet that boosts the
power of Dark-type moves.

iron-plate.name: Iron Plate
iron-plate.effect:
An item to be held by a Pokémon.
It is a stone tablet that boosts the
power of Steel-type moves.

odd-incense.name: Odd Incense
odd-incense.effect:
An item to be held by a Pokémon. It
is
an exotic-smelling incense that
boosts
the power of Psychic-type moves.

rock-incense.name: Rock Incense
rock-incense.effect:
An item to be held by a Pokémon. It
is
an exotic-smelling incense that
boosts
the power of Rock-type moves.

full-incense.name: Full Incense
full-incense.effect:
An item to be held by a Pokémon. It
is
an exotic-smelling incense that makes
the holder bloated and slow moving.

wave-incense.name: Wave Incense
wave-incense.effect:
An item to be held by a Pokémon. It
is
an exotic-smelling incense that
boosts
the power of Water-type moves.

rose-incense.name: Rose Incense
rose-incense.effect:
An item to be held by a Pokémon. It
is
an exotic-smelling incense that
boosts
the power of Grass-type moves.

luck-incense.name: Luck Incense
luck-incense.effect:
An item to be held by a Pokémon.
It doubles a battle's prize money if
the holding Pokémon joins in.

pure-incense.name: Pure Incense
pure-incense.effect:
An item to be held by a Pokémon.
It helps keep wild Pokémon away if
the
holder is the first one in the party.

protector.name: Protector
protector.effect:
A protective item of some sort.
It is extremely stiff and heavy.
It is loved by a certain Pokémon.

electirizer.name: Electirizer
electirizer.effect:
A box packed with a tremendous
amount of electric energy.
It is loved by a certain Pokémon.

magmarizer.name: Magmarizer
magmarizer.effect:
A box packed with a tremendous
amount of magma energy.
It is loved by a certain Pokémon.

dubious-disc.name: Dubious Disc
dubious-disc.effect:
A transparent device overflowing with
dubious data.
Its producer is unknown.

reaper-cloth.name: Reaper Cloth
reaper-cloth.effect:
A cloth imbued with horrifyingly
strong
spiritual energy.
It is loved by a certain Pokémon.

razor-claw.name: Razor Claw
razor-claw.effect:
An item to be held by a Pokémon.
It is a sharply hooked claw that ups
the holder's critical-hit ratio.

razor-fang.name: Razor Fang
razor-fang.effect:
An item to be held by a Pokémon.
It may cause the foe to flinch when
the holder inflicts damage.

tm---hone-claws.name: TM - Hone Claws
tm---hone-claws.effect:
The user sharpens its claws to boost
its Attack stat and accuracy.

tm---psyshock.name: TM - Psyshock
tm---psyshock.effect:
The user materializes an odd psychic
wave to attack the target. This
attack does physical damage.

tm---venoshock.name: TM - Venoshock
tm---venoshock.effect:
The user drenches the target in a
special poisonous liquid. Its power
is doubled if the target is
poisoned.

tm---telekinesis.name: TM - Telekinesis
tm---telekinesis.effect:
The user makes the target float with
its psychic power. The target is
easier to hit for three turns.

tm---smack-down.name: TM - Smack Down
tm---smack-down.effect:
The user throws a stone or
projectile to attack an opponent. A
flying Pokémon will fall to the
ground when hit.

tm---sludge-wave.name: TM - Sludge Wave
tm---sludge-wave.effect:
It swamps the area around the user
with a giant sludge wave. It may
also poison those hit.

tm---flame-charge.name: TM - Flame Charge
tm---flame-charge.effect:
The user cloaks itself with flame
and attacks. Building up more
power, it raises the user's Speed
stat.

tm---low-sweep.name: TM - Low Sweep
tm---low-sweep.effect:
The user attacks the target's legs
swiftly, reducing the target's
Speed stat.

tm---round.name: TM - Round
tm---round.effect:
The user attacks the target with a
song. Others can join in the Round
and make the attack do greater
damage.

tm---echoed-voice.name: TM - Echoed Voice
tm---echoed-voice.effect:
The user attacks the target with an
echoing voice. If this move is used
every turn, it does greater
damage.

tm---ally-switch.name: TM - Ally Switch
tm---ally-switch.effect:
The user teleports, switching places
with its adjacent ally. It may fail
if used consecutively.

tm---focus-blast.name: TM - Focus Blast
tm---focus-blast.effect:
The user heightens its mental focus
and unleashes its power. It may
also lower the target's Sp. Def.

tm---energy-ball.name: TM - Energy Ball
tm---energy-ball.effect:
The user draws power from nature and
fires it at the target. It may also
lower the target's Sp. Def.

tm---false-swipe.name: TM - False Swipe
tm---false-swipe.effect:
A restrained attack that prevents
the target from fainting. The
target is left with at least 1 HP.

tm---scald.name: TM - Scald
tm---scald.effect:
The user shoots boiling hot water at
its target. It may also leave the
target with a burn.

tm---fling.name: TM - Fling
tm---fling.effect:
The user flings its item at the foe,
destroying it. In PvP, only
consumable items are destroyed
permanently. The move's power and
effects vary depending on what item
is thrown.

tm---charge-beam.name: TM - Charge Beam
tm---charge-beam.effect:
The user attacks with an electric
charge. The user may use any
remaining electricity to raise its
Sp. Atk stat.

tm---sky-drop.name: TM - Sky Drop
tm---sky-drop.effect:
The user takes the target into the
sky, then drops it during the next
turn. The target cannot attack
while in the sky.

tm---incinerate.name: TM - Incinerate
tm---incinerate.effect:
The user attacks the target with
fire. If the target is holding a
Berry, the Berry becomes burnt up
and unusable.

tm---quash.name: TM - Quash
tm---quash.effect:
The user suppresses the target and
makes its move go last.

tm---will-o-wisp.name: TM - Will-O-Wisp
tm---will-o-wisp.effect:
The user shoots a sinister,
bluish-white flame at the target to
inflict a burn.

tm---acrobatics.name: TM - Acrobatics
tm---acrobatics.effect:
The user nimbly strikes the target.
If the user is not holding an item,
this attack inflicts massive
damage.

tm---embargo.name: TM - Embargo
tm---embargo.effect:
It prevents the target from using
its held item. Its Trainer is also
prevented from using items on it.

tm---explosion.name: TM - Explosion
tm---explosion.effect:
The user explodes to inflict damage
on those around it. The user faints
upon using this move.

tm---shadow-claw.name: TM - Shadow Claw
tm---shadow-claw.effect:
The user slashes with a sharp claw
made from shadows. Critical hits
land more easily.

tm---payback.name: TM - Payback
tm---payback.effect:
If the user moves after the target,
this attack's power will be
doubled.

tm---retaliate.name: TM - Retaliate
tm---retaliate.effect:
The user gets revenge for a fainted
ally. If an ally fainted in the
previous turn, this attack's damage
increases.

tm---giga-impact.name: TM - Giga Impact
tm---giga-impact.effect:
The user charges at the target using
every bit of its power. The user
must rest on the next turn.

tm---rock-polish.name: TM - Rock Polish
tm---rock-polish.effect:
The user polishes its body to reduce
drag. It can sharply raise the
Speed stat.

tm---flash.name: TM - Flash
tm---flash.effect:
The user flashes a bright light that
cuts the target's accuracy. It can
also be used to illuminate caves.

tm---stone-edge.name: TM - Stone Edge
tm---stone-edge.effect:
The user stabs the foe with
sharpened stones from below. It has
a high critical-hit ratio.

tm---volt-switch.name: TM - Volt Switch
tm---volt-switch.effect:
After making its attack, the user
rushes back to switch places with a
party Pokémon in waiting.

tm---thunder-wave.name: TM - Thunder Wave
tm---thunder-wave.effect:
A weak electric charge is launched
at the target. It causes paralysis
if it hits.

tm---gyro-ball.name: TM - Gyro Ball
tm---gyro-ball.effect:
The user tackles the target with a
high-speed spin. The slower the
user, the greater the damage.

tm---swords-dance.name: TM - Swords Dance
tm---swords-dance.effect:
A frenetic dance to uplift the
fighting spirit. It sharply raises
the user's Attack stat.

tm---struggle-bug.name: TM - Struggle Bug
tm---struggle-bug.effect:
While resisting, the user attacks
the opposing Pokémon. The targets'
Sp. Atk stat is reduced.

tm---psych-up.name: TM - Psych Up
tm---psych-up.effect:
The user hypnotizes itself into
copying any stat change made by the
target.

tm---bulldoze.name: TM - Bulldoze
tm---bulldoze.effect:
The user stomps down on the ground
and attacks everything in the area.
Hit Pokémon's Speed stat is
reduced.

tm---frost-breath.name: TM - Frost Breath
tm---frost-breath.effect:
The user blows a cold breath on the
target. This attack always results
in a critical hit.

tm---rock-slide.name: TM - Rock Slide
tm---rock-slide.effect:
Large boulders are hurled at the
opposing team to inflict damage. It
may also make the targets flinch.

tm---x-scissor.name: TM - X-Scissor
tm---x-scissor.effect:
The user slashes at the target by
crossing its scythes or claws as if
they were a pair of scissors.

tm---dragon-tail.name: TM - Dragon Tail
tm---dragon-tail.effect:
The user knocks away the target and
drags out another Pokémon in its
party. In the wild, the battle
ends.

tm---work-up.name: TM - Work Up
tm---work-up.effect:
The user is roused, and its Attack
and Sp. Atk stats increase.

tm---poison-jab.name: TM - Poison Jab
tm---poison-jab.effect:
The target is stabbed with a
tentacle or arm steeped in poison.
It may also poison the target.

tm---dream-eater.name: TM - Dream Eater
tm---dream-eater.effect:
The user eats the dreams of a
sleeping target. It absorbs half
the damage caused to heal the
user's HP.

tm---grass-knot.name: TM - Grass Knot
tm---grass-knot.effect:
The user snares the target with
grass and trips it. The heavier the
target, the greater the damage.

tm---swagger.name: TM - Swagger
tm---swagger.effect:
The user enrages and confuses the
target. However, it also sharply
raises the target's Attack stat.

tm---pluck.name: TM - Pluck
tm---pluck.effect:
The user pecks the target. If the
target is holding a Berry, the user
eats it and gains its effect.

tm---u-turn.name: TM - U-turn
tm---u-turn.effect:
After making its attack, the user
rushes back to switch places with a
party Pokémon in waiting.

tm---substitute.name: TM - Substitute
tm---substitute.effect:
The user makes a copy of itself
using some of its HP. The copy
serves as the user's decoy.

tm---flash-cannon.name: TM - Flash Cannon
tm---flash-cannon.effect:
The user gathers all its light
energy and releases it at once. It
may also lower the target's Sp. Def
stat.

tm---trick-room.name: TM - Trick Room
tm---trick-room.effect:
The user creates a bizarre area in
which slower Pokémon get to move
first for five turns.

explorer-kit.name: Explorer Kit
explorer-kit.effect:
A bag filled with convenient tools
for exploring. It provides access to
the Underground.

loot-sack.name: Loot Sack
loot-sack.effect:
A sturdy, spacious bag that is used
to carry loot obtained in the coal
mine.

rule-book.name: Rule Book
rule-book.effect:
It lists the rules for holding
battles.
For linked battles, you may choose
which set of rules you wish to use.

poké-radar.name: Poké Radar
poké-radar.effect:
A tool that can search out Pokémon
that are hiding in grass. Its battery
is
recharged as you walk.

point-card.name: Point Card
point-card.effect:
A card that lists the Battle Points
you have earned.

journal.name: Journal
journal.effect:
A notebook that keeps a day-to-day
record of your adventure so far.

seal-case.name: Seal Case
seal-case.effect:
A case for storing Seals that can be
applied to the Capsule cases of
Poké Balls.

fashion-case.name: Fashion Case
fashion-case.effect:
A fancy case for the tidy arrangement
and storage of whimsical Pokémon
Accessories.

seal-bag.name: Seal Bag
seal-bag.effect:
A tiny bag that can hold ten Seals
for
decorating Poké Balls.

pal-pad.name: Pal Pad
pal-pad.effect:
A convenient notepad that is used for
registering your friends, Friend
Codes,
and keeping a record of game play.

works-key.name: Works Key
works-key.effect:
A large key for operating the doors
of
the Valley Windworks in the canyon.
It was held by a Team Galactic Grunt.

old-charm.name: Old Charm
old-charm.effect:
An ancient good-luck charm made of
Pokémon bones to be taken to the
elder
of Celestic Town.

galactic-key.name: Galactic Key
galactic-key.effect:
A card key for disengaging security
systems in the Galactic HQ. Losing it
can result in punishment, apparently.

red-chain.name: Red Chain
red-chain.effect:
A mythical chain that is said to link
the legendary Pokémon that created
the Sinnoh region.

vs.-seeker.name: Vs. Seeker
vs.-seeker.effect:
A device that indicates Trainers who
want to battle. Its battery charges
while you walk.

sprayduck.name: Sprayduck
sprayduck.effect:
A watering can shaped like a PSYDUCK.
It helps promote healthy growth of
Berries planted in soft soil.

poffin-case.name: Poffin Case
poffin-case.effect:
A case for storing Poffin cooked from
Berries.

suite-key.name: Suite Key
suite-key.effect:
A key to one of the suites at the
luxury hotel by a lake. For some odd
reason, it often disappears.

oak's-letter.name: Oak's Letter
oak's-letter.effect:
A letter from Prof. Oak.
Written in it is a request for you to
go to Rt. 224.

lunar-wing.name: Lunar Wing
lunar-wing.effect:
A feather that glows like the moon.
It is said to possess the power to
dispel nightmares.

member-card.name: Member Card
member-card.effect:
A card needed for entering the inn in
Canalave City. Oddly, the last date
marked on it was 50 years ago.

azure-flute.name: Azure Flute
azure-flute.effect:
A flute that puts out echoing sounds
that do not seem to be of this world.
It is unknown who made it.

magma-stone.name: Magma Stone
magma-stone.effect:
A stone formed when boulders melted
in
intensely hot magma, then hardened.
Magma remains sealed inside.

parcel.name: Parcel
parcel.effect:
A parcel entrusted in your care.
You are supposed to deliver it to
your
childhood friend who left Twinleaf
Town.

coupon-1.name: Coupon 1
coupon-1.effect:
A coupon to be exchanged for a
Pokémon Watch (Pokétch for short).
Three coupons are needed.

coupon-2.name: Coupon 2
coupon-2.effect:
A coupon to be exchanged for a
Pokémon Watch (Pokétch for short).
Three coupons are needed.

coupon-3.name: Coupon 3
coupon-3.effect:
A coupon to be exchanged for a
Pokémon Watch (Pokétch for short).
Three coupons are needed.

secretpotion.name: SecretPotion
secretpotion.effect:
A fantastic medicine dispensed by the
pharmacy in Cianwood City. It fully
heals a Pokémon of any ailment.

vs.-recorder.name: Vs. Recorder
vs.-recorder.effect:
An amazing device that can record a
battle either between friends or at a
special battle facility.

apricorn-box.name: Apricorn Box
apricorn-box.effect:
A handy box where you can store up to
99 Apricorns of each kind.

unown-report.name: UNOWN Report
unown-report.effect:
A report of all the discovered kinds
of UNOWN.

berry-pots.name: Berry Pots
berry-pots.effect:
Handy containers for cultivating
Berries wherever you go.

dowsing-mchn.name: Dowsing MCHN
dowsing-mchn.effect:
It checks for unseen items in the
area
and makes noise and lights when it
finds something.

blue-card.name: Blue Card
blue-card.effect:
A card to save points for the
Buena's Password show.

slowpoketail.name: SlowpokeTail
slowpoketail.effect:
A very tasty tail of something.
It sells for a high price.

clear-bell.name: Clear Bell
clear-bell.effect:
A very old-fashioned bell that makes
a
gentle ringing.

squirtbottle.name: SquirtBottle
squirtbottle.effect:
A bottle used for watering plants in
the
Berry Pots.

red-scale.name: Red Scale
red-scale.effect:
A scale from the red GYARADOS. It
glows
red like a flame.

lost-item.name: Lost Item
lost-item.effect: The Poké Doll lost by the Copycat.

pass.name: Pass
pass.effect:
A ticket required for riding the
Magnet
Train. It allows you to ride whenever
and however much you'd like.

machine-part.name: Machine Part
machine-part.effect:
An important machine part for the
Power Plant that was stolen.

silver-wing.name: Silver Wing
silver-wing.effect:
A strange, silvery feather
that sparkles.

rainbow-wing.name: Rainbow Wing
rainbow-wing.effect:
A mystical, rainbow feather
that sparkles.

mystery-egg.name: Mystery Egg
mystery-egg.effect:
A mysterious Egg obtained from Mr.
Pokémon. What's in the Egg is
unknown.

red-apricorn.name: Red Apricorn
red-apricorn.effect:
A red Apricorn.
It assails your nostrils.

blu-apricorn.name: Blu Apricorn
blu-apricorn.effect:
A blue Apricorn.
It smells a bit like grass.

ylw-apricorn.name: Ylw Apricorn
ylw-apricorn.effect:
A yellow Apricorn.
It has an invigorating scent.

grn-apricorn.name: Grn Apricorn
grn-apricorn.effect:
A green Apricorn.
It has a mysterious, aromatic scent.

pnk-apricorn.name: Pnk Apricorn
pnk-apricorn.effect:
A pink Apricorn.
It has a nice, sweet scent.

wht-apricorn.name: Wht Apricorn
wht-apricorn.effect:
A white Apricorn.
It doesn't smell like anything.

blk-apricorn.name: Blk Apricorn
blk-apricorn.effect:
A black Apricorn
It has an indescribable scent.

fast-ball.name: Fast Ball
fast-ball.effect:
A Poké Ball that makes it easier to
catch fast Pokémon.

level-ball.name: Level Ball
level-ball.effect:
A Poké Ball for catching Pokémon that
are a lower level than your own.

lure-ball.name: Lure Ball
lure-ball.effect:
A Poké Ball for catching Pokémon
hooked
by a Rod when fishing.

heavy-ball.name: Heavy Ball
heavy-ball.effect:
A Poké Ball for catching very heavy
Pokémon.

love-ball.name: Love Ball
love-ball.effect:
